('chunk_4cd3907ad5204975ad','file_635d854e419faefdf1','pahe.md','Common Misconceptions — Master List','| # | Misconception | Correction |
|---|--------------|-----------|
| 1 | First aid means fully treating/curing the injury yourself | First aid is **temporary stabilising care** until professional help arrives |
| 2 | A bruise means the skin is broken | A bruise is bleeding **under intact skin** — no open wound |
| 3 | Put heat on a fresh injury | Fresh soft-tissue injuries need **cold (ice)**; heat comes later once swelling is gone |
| 4 | Ice can stay on as long as it feels good | Limit ice to **~15–20 minutes**; wrap it — never on bare skin |
| 5 | Sprain and strain are the same | **Sprain = ligament** (bone-to-bone); **strain = muscle/tendon** |
| 6 | "No pain, no gain" — push through all pain | Effort is normal; **sharp/persistent pain is a warning** of injury (often overuse) |
| 7 | You can run any distance while holding the handball | Only **up to 3 steps** without dribbling; no double-dribble |
| 8 | The hardest pass is the best pass | The **most catchable, appropriate** pass is best |
| 9 | Every race starts with block/crouch start | **Blocks for short sprints**; distance races use **standing starts** |
| 10 | Stand up straight as fast as possible out of the blocks | Stay **low with forward lean in the drive phase**; rise gradually |
| 11 | A fast start is just leg strength | Needs **several components** — power, reaction time, core stability, flexibility |
| 12 | Yoga is just modern stretching | Yoga is a **thousands-of-years-old** practice of body, breath and mind |
| 13 | You must be flexible to start yoga | Flexibility is a **result**, not a requirement |
| 14 | Yoga is only the poses | Poses are **one of eight limbs** |
| 15 | Everyone should do full lotus quickly | Padmasana needs open hips; forcing it risks **knee injury** — progress via half lotus |

---','{"common":1,"misconceptions":1,"master":1,"list":1,"misconception":1,"correction":1,"first":2,"aid":2,"means":2,"fully":1,"treating":1,"curing":1,"the":10,"injury":4,"yourself":1,"temporary":1,"stabilising":1,"care":1,"until":1,"professional":1,"help":1,"arrives":1,"bruise":2,"skin":3,"broken":1,"bleeding":1,"under":1,"intact":1,"open":2,"wound":1,"put":1,"heat":2,"fresh":2,"soft":1,"tissue":1,"injuries":1,"need":1,"cold":1,"ice":3,"comes":1,"later":1,"once":1,"swelling":1,"gone":1,"can":2,"stay":2,"long":1,"feels":1,"good":1,"limit":1,"minutes":1,"wrap":1,"never":1,"bare":1,"sprain":2,"and":2,"strain":2,"are":2,"same":1,"ligament":1,"bone":2,"muscle":1,"tendon":1,"pain":3,"gain":1,"push":1,"through":1,"all":1,"effort":1,"normal":1,"sharp":1,"persistent":1,"warning":1,"often":1,"overuse":1,"you":2,"run":1,"any":1,"distance":2,"while":1,"holding":1,"handball":1,"only":2,"steps":1,"without":1,"dribbling":1,"double":1,"dribble":1,"hardest":1,"pass":3,"best":2,"most":1,"catchable":1,"appropriate":1,"every":1,"race":1,"starts":2,"with":2,"block":1,"crouch":1,"start":3,"blocks":2,"for":1,"short":1,"sprints":1,"races":1,"use":1,"standing":1,"stand":1,"straight":1,"fast":2,"possible":1,"out":1,"low":1,"forward":1,"lean":1,"drive":1,"phase":1,"rise":1,"gradually":1,"just":2,"leg":1,"strength":1,"needs":2,"several":1,"components":1,"power":1,"reaction":1,"time":1,"core":1,"stability":1,"flexibility":2,"yoga":4,"modern":1,"stretching":1,"thousands":1,"years":1,"old":1,"practice":1,"body":1,"breath":1,"mind":1,"must":1,"flexible":1,"result":1,"not":1,"requirement":1,"poses":2,"one":1,"eight":1,"limbs":1,"everyone":1,"should":1,"full":1,"lotus":2,"quickly":1,"padmasana":1,"hips":1,"forcing":1,"risks":1,"knee":1,"progress":1,"via":1,"half":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_da10b931611cb4d54e','file_635d854e419faefdf1','pahe.md','Command-Term / Reflection Question Bank','1. **State** the five steps of PRICE and explain the purpose of each. *(Criterion A)*
2. **Compare** a sprain and a strain, naming the tissue and typical site of each. *(Criterion A)*
3. **Design** a short warm-up plan that reduces the risk of acute and overuse injuries for a handball session, and **justify** your choices. *(Criterion B)*
4. **Demonstrate** a controlled dribble and an accurate overarm pass, then **describe** the key technique cues you used. *(Criterion C)*
5. **Evaluate** which fitness component matters most for a fast sprint start, using evidence from your own practice. *(Criterion A/D)*
6. **Reflect** on your performance in the block start: which phase was strongest, which needs work, and what will you change next time? *(Criterion D)*
7. **Discuss** whether individual skill or team communication is more important in an invasion game like handball. *(Criterion A)*
8. **Explain** how yoga develops balance between the physical body and the mind, referring to at least two of the Eight Limbs. *(Criterion A/D)*

