('chunk_580d98174e02cdb491','file_635d854e419faefdf1','pahe.md','Cross-Subject Connections','- **Sciences – Biology:** Muscles, tendons, ligaments and joints (sprains/strains); the skin as an organ and wound healing; the respiratory system and breath control (pranayama); how the body adapts to training. Links to PHE related concepts *systems, function, adaptation*.
- **Sciences – Physics:** Forces, friction and Newton''s laws in the sprint start (pushing against blocks/ground → forward motion); power = force × velocity; levers and leverage in the staggered stance; balance and centre of gravity in yoga poses. Links to *energy, movement, balance*.
- **Language & Literature / Language Acquisition:** Reflection and evaluation writing (Criterion D); using accurate command terms (state, describe, explain, evaluate); writing clear first-aid instructions and self-reflections; presenting the history of handball or yoga. Links to *communication, perspective*.
- **Individuals & Societies:** The global history and cultural spread of handball and yoga (Personal and cultural expression; Globalization).

