('chunk_b9228bff52fbb3e1ac','file_8378b145fc1fad06fd','physics.md','How to read this file','The structure is **Unit → Sub-topic (chapter) → concept entries**. Each unit opens with its Key Concept, Related Concepts, Global Context, Statement of Inquiry, and three inquiry questions. Each concept entry gives a definition, a real-world example, an analogy, why it matters, a described diagram or worked example where useful, at least one misconception, and three command-term questions graded from recall to analyse/evaluate.

